Higher Health CEO, Ramneek Ahluwalia spoke with eNCA's Uveka Rangappa. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Higher Health is urging this year's first year and returning students to prioritise their health. It's warning historical health challenges such as HIV, substance abuse and mental health issues have been exacerbated by the COVID-19 pandemic. READ: Students vow to continue protesting over funding, debt Higher Health is an agency of the Higher Education Department focussed on student health and wellbeing. Higher Health CEO Ramneek Ahluwalia said mental health is real. 080 036 3636, this is a toll-free Higher Help crisis helpline for mental health and for gender-based violence. Watch the video above for more details